# Known pre-existing api-layer import violations — grandfathered by
# scripts/check_api_layer_imports.py pending the full-move refactor
# tracked in issue #541.
#
# The CI check FAILS on any NEW file under src/datapulse/ that imports
# from datapulse.api.* (outside src/datapulse/api/ itself), and PRINTS
# A WARNING for listed files so the debt stays visible.
#
# Why these are grandfathered: each path below imports a FastAPI-dep
# symbol (get_current_user / get_tenant_session / get_tenant_plan_limits)
# that currently lives in api/ for wiring reasons. Moving those symbols
# to core/ would break ~15 tests that patch("datapulse.api.auth...") /
# patch("datapulse.api.deps...") — a file-move refactor best done as its
# own PR. See docs/brain/decisions/ for the full rationale.
#
# Procedure to remove an entry:
# 1. Move the referenced symbol to datapulse.core.* (or another allowed
#    layer per .claude/rules/datapulse-graph.md).
# 2. Re-export via datapulse.api.* for backwards compatibility, OR update
#    the patch targets in every test that mocks the old location.
# 3. Run: python scripts/check_api_layer_imports.py — file should drop
#    out of the WARNING set. Delete the matching line below.
#
# Format: one POSIX-style repo-relative path per line,
#         comments start with '#', blank lines OK.

src/datapulse/billing/pos_guard.py
src/datapulse/pos/devices.py
src/datapulse/pos/idempotency.py
src/datapulse/pos/overrides.py
src/datapulse/rbac/dependencies.py
